<br>
Fine tuning tactics is fine when there is not competition for a spawn.  As you said, 10 percent is damn close and you probably could have gotten the mob given enough tries.  Hell you might not even need better tactics, just a better swing of the random number generator.<br>
<br>
The problem with continually wiping while others are standing there waiting is that you are wasting the time of quite a few people, those in your party who cannot beat the thing, and those in the opposing party(ies) who can't even take a shot even if they could easily kill the critter.<br>
<br>
Who is in the right?  The people treading water or wiping while they wait for more of their friends to show up, or those that get tired of waiting and claim the spawn as their own?  I would side with first in force, I don't believe in wasting my friends time or other peoples time.<br>
<br>
Thats what makes mobs like the Arbitor in Earth, or Avatar of War in Kael so nice.  They are a supreme pain in the ass because realistically you only get one shot.  There is no kill stealing to worry about.  If you fail no one has time for another go.  Arbitor is one of the most difficult encounters I have ever seen, the timer is absurd and he is a very tough fight.  You have to do alot of things perfectly just to get a shot at him and even then he still might kick your ass.<br>
<br>
